               <p>MR. BARRY conducted the prosecution.</p>
               <p>RICHARD LEVETT. I am an <rs id="t18270531-287-viclabel1545" type="occupation">ironmonger</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270531-287-victim1569 t18270531-287-viclabel1545"></join>, and live in Broad-street, Ratcliff. On the 16th of April the prisoner called at my shop, and said he was directed by a lady in the neighbourhood to get a coal-scuttle, kettle, and teapot, and would I let her have two of each to show her, and she would return one of each in half an hour - he said"I expect you will give me a few shillings for my trouble." I knew him before; he took the goods, and never returned. I did not see him again till yesterday - I wrote down the prices by his desire - my man delivered them to him.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I buy goods on commission - I sold them to a person who owes me 16l. - I cannot get the money for them.</p>
               <p>RICHARD LEVETT. I never dealt with him before.</p>
               <p>
